text: Mersey Care NHS Foundation Trust have had five deaths related to Covid-19 and all patients that passed away had pre-existing conditions.
The deaths of 181 NHS workers have involved Covid-19.
To the end of 2021, there have been 18,939 Covid-19 deaths with comorbidities in the UK.
There were five deaths within 28 days of a positive Covid-19 test in the UK.
Official NHS data to 16 July shows there were 1,379 Covid-19 deaths in which there were no pre-existing conditions.
According to NHS data, as of 21st January there have been 4,717 Covid-19 deaths of people between the ages of 0-59 in the UK.
At least 133 children have died of Covid-19 in the UK.
To the end of 2021, there have been 156,924 deaths within 28 days of a positive Covid-19 test in the UK.
Around 17,000 people have died of Covid-19 in Britain.
From 21 July to 25 July the UK reported 426 Covid-19 deaths.
To the end of 2021, there have been 6,189 Covid-19 deaths where only Covid-19 was entered on the death certificate.
The deaths of 131 care workers have involved Covid-19.
The UK recorded just three deaths from respiratory conditions besides Covid-19 in October 2020.
Only hundreds, not thousands, of people have died of Covid without any other pre-existing condition mentioned on their death certificate.
According to NHS England figures, the number of people whose death certificates show death from only coronavirus, i.e. no pre-existing condition, is 1,265.
18 people died of Covid-19 in one day in England.
